This paper investigates the impact of micro-packages in the npm JavaScript ecosystem, which is a software engineering discipline. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category. The paper also involves analyzing dependencies and usage costs, which could fall under cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The study uses empirical methods, which could also fit under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
